            },
            "answer_text": "The base most commonly found in an American home is baking soda, Sodium bicarbonate, used by itself or in combination with other ingredients to make baking powder. Probably the next most common is lye, Sodium hydroxide, used in a variety of cleaning products, from drain cleaners to oven cleaners. ",
